Date: Wed, 01 Dec 1999 23:21:38 -0500
From: Sudhir Reddy <Sudhir.Reddy@Merial.com>

I hail from Andhra Pradesh and I still have strong roots in India. Although
it leaves [me totally flabbergasted, the news of "public resistance or
indifference to vaccination owing to religious reasons", saddens me.
I can assure you though, that in the urban and rural areas where I have
lived for almost 25 years, I have only seen people scrambling to get
vaccinated. Government hospitals offer vaccinations free of cost to
increase public health awareness among the masses. In a country where
vaccinations are as well received as the popular adage itself, "PREVENTION
IS BETTER THAN CURE", this day in age, I find the news very hard to believe.
--
Sudhir K. Reddy, BVSc&AH, MVetSci, PhD
Senior Research Microbiologist
Biological Product Development
Merial Limited
115 Transtech Drive
Athens, GA 30606
